<typeStatus id="54DCEFA6FF89FF911CB7FA67FE8AF0C8" box="[199,308,1496,1522]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Holotype</typeStatus>
female description
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135C4D81FF89FF911E59FA67FDD3F0C8" box="[553,621,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1625,1952]" captionTargetId="figure-380@6.[151,1436,1618,1959]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 9. Holotype of Robinsonia marahensis Laguerrre sp. nov., dorsal view on the left and ventral view on the right, labels are not to scale. Scale = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982852/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF89FF911EF5FA67FCFAF0C8" box="[645,836,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Head and thorax</emphasis>
. Antennae shortly bipectinate, shaft and rami brown, greyish beige at base, scape whitish. Frons dirty white, vertex pure white. Patagia, tegulae and thorax, white. Palpi dirty white underside, yellowish upper side, third segment very short.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF18018CFF89FF911CE7F801FE63F2C0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982852" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4982852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982852/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" startId="6.[151,250,1982,2006]" targetBox="[159,1427,1625,1952]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF89FF911CE7F801FE63F2C0" blockId="6.[151,1436,1982,2043]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF89FF911CE7F801FEACF2ED" bold="true" box="[151,274,1982,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">FIGURE 9.</emphasis>
Holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF89FF911DE6F800FD50F2ED" authority="Laguerrre" authorityName="Laguerrre" authorityYear="2021" box="[406,750,1983,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marahensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF89FF911DE6F800FD3AF2ED" box="[406,644,1983,2007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Robinsonia marahensis</emphasis>
Laguerrre
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A220306DFF89FF911E83F800FCFAF2EC" box="[755,836,1983,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF89FF911E83F800FC80F2ED" bold="true" box="[755,830,1983,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, dorsal view on the left and ventral view on the right, labels are not to scale. Scale = 10 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FF28FDBEF5EF" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FF28FF42F58A" box="[199,252,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Legs</emphasis>
. Anterior coxae pure white. First pair of legs light brownish grey. Second and third pairs dirty white below with a brownish grey upperside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FF60FB29F47B" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FF60FE8DF5C2" box="[199,307,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Forewing</emphasis>
. Wings rounded with a straight termen, entirely silky white. The costa up to the apex is covered by a narrow black line bordered inside by a greyish line. Below similar to upper side but the costa very narrowly black at base then widening toward apex, bordered internally by dirty greyish white until the cell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FEF4FBF9F45F" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,1095,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FEF4FE8BF45F" box="[199,309,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Hindwing</emphasis>
. Rounded wings entirely silky white. Underside similar to upper side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FED0FBBCF4B3" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,1026,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FED0FE8FF4B3" box="[199,305,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Silky white and hairy upper side and creamy yellow underside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FE2CFD89F497" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,567,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
Forewing length: 
<quantity id="4C9FFCE1FF88FF901DFEFE2CFE63F497" box="[398,477,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
(n = 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FE08FE3DF4EB" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,387,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FE08FEBAF4EB" bold="true" box="[199,260,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Male</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FE64FB54F75B" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,609]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FE64FE30F4CE" bold="true" box="[199,398,474,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="135C4D81FF88FF901DEEFE64FD97F4CF" box="[414,553,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1272,1296]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,633,1249]" captionTargetId="figure-197@7.[151,1436,633,1249]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 10. A–C: female genitalia of Robinsonia maranhensis Laguerre sp. nov., A ventral view, B dorsal view, C detail of the antrum, ductus bursae and papillae anales." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982854/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Fig. 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Papilles anales subrectangular, concave in middle. Apophyses very thin, the anteriores shorter than the posteriores. Pheromone glands tubular. Antrum slightly sclerotized shaped as a flat “U”. Ductus bursae as a flat ribbon, sharply bent near extremity and with a narrow fold in middle. Bursa copulatrix hemispherical entirely covered with tiny spicules. In the last third two small circular and concave signa.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF18018CFF88FF901CE7FB47FDD4F00E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982854" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4982854" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982854/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" startId="7.[151,250,1272,1296]" targetBox="[151,1436,633,1249]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CE7FB47FDD4F00E" blockId="7.[151,1436,1272,1332]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CE7FB47FEE9F02A" bold="true" box="[151,343,1272,1296]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">FIGURE 10. A–C</emphasis>
: female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF88FF901E5BFB47FC37F02B" authority="Laguerre" authorityName="Laguerre" authorityYear="2021" box="[555,905,1272,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maranhensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901E5BFB47FC98F02A" box="[555,806,1272,1296]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Robinsonia maranhensis</emphasis>
Laguerre
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A220306DFF88FF901FE0FB46FC5DF02A" box="[912,995,1273,1297]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901FE0FB46FC62F02B" bold="true" box="[912,988,1273,1297]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901F80FB47FBBCF02A" bold="true" box="[1008,1026,1272,1296]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">A</emphasis>
ventral view, 
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF9018E4FB46FB1BF02B" bold="true" box="[1172,1189,1273,1297]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">B</emphasis>
dorsal view, 
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF90195FFB47FAFFF02A" bold="true" box="[1327,1345,1272,1296]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">C</emphasis>
detail of the antrum, ductus bursae and papillae anales.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FADCFE63F047" blockId="7.[151,1436,1379,1513]" box="[199,477,1379,1405]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FADCFEE7F047" bold="true" box="[199,345,1379,1405]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Early stages</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FA38FC01F09B" blockId="7.[151,1436,1379,1513]" box="[199,959,1415,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FA38FEF0F09B" bold="true" box="[199,334,1415,1441]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named by reference to the original locality: 
<collectingRegion id="49A39FE6FF88FF901F36FA38FC05F09B" box="[838,955,1415,1441]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Marañhao</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CB7FA15FEFDF0D3" blockId="7.[151,1436,1379,1513]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901CB7FA15FEDFF0FE" bold="true" box="[199,353,1450,1476]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Distribution.</emphasis>
Presently only known from the 
<collectingRegion id="49A39FE6FF88FF901EB9FA14FCC6F0FF" box="[713,888,1451,1477]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Marañhao state</collectingRegion>
, near the border with 
<collectingRegion id="49A39FE6FF88FF90181CFA14FB1FF0FF" box="[1132,1185,1451,1477]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Parà</collectingRegion>
, an area with a largely endemic fauna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD85104FF88FF901CE7F9A8FAA6F3DF" blockId="7.[151,1437,1559,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
During the past 10 years I have received from Ulf Drechsel (
<collectingCountry id="F3701194FF88FF901F5EF9A8FC24F30B" box="[814,922,1559,1585]" name="Paraguay" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
) some scattered specimens of a small whithish inconspicuous Arctiinae which identification proved to be very difficult. Finally 
<specimenCount id="9D619A8DFF88FF90185DF984FB5DF36F" box="[1069,1251,1595,1621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount id="9D619A8DFF88FF901883F984FA9EF36F" box="[1267,1312,1595,1621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="male">2 ♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount id="9D619A8DFF88FF901958F984FAECF36F" box="[1320,1362,1595,1621]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" type="female">1 ♀</specimenCount>
) were sequenced and, to our surprise, the sequences nicely align within the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF88FF901F8FF9E0FBC1F343" authorityName="Laguerre" authorityYear="2021" box="[1023,1151,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901F8FF9E0FBC1F343" box="[1023,1151,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Robinsonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not far from 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF88FF90196DF9E0FE12F3A7" authority="Rothschild, 1910" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klagesi">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF90196DF9E0FF58F3A7" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Robinsonia klagesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF62CF5FF88FF901C9DF93CFE12F3A7" author="Rothschild" box="[237,428,1667,1693]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 85" refId="ref8683" refString="Rothschild, = L. W. = (1910) Catalogue of Arctianae in the Tring Museum, with notes and descriptions of new species. Novitates Zoologicae, 17, 1 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 13688" type="journal article" year="1910">Rothschild, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(7.8 %) or 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF88FF901E5AF93CFC08F3A7" authority="Rothschild, 1922" authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1922" box="[554,950,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mossi">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901E5AF93CFD4FF3A6" box="[554,753,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Robinsonia mossi</emphasis>
Rothschild, 1922
</taxonomicName>
(5.7 %), two well known species present in 
<collectingCountry id="F3701194FF88FF901CE7F918FE83F3FB" box="[151,317,1703,1729]" name="French Guiana" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
but with totally different habitus (see 
<figureCitation id="135C4D81FF88FF901E99F918FC92F3FB" box="[745,812,1703,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1655,1679]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,1218,1628]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,1213,1631]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbour-Joining tree of 17 selected COX1 sequences of the studied group, distances in % are given below each branch and bootstrap supports are given above each branch in bold (only if larger than 70 %) (obtained with MEGA7, see Ku- maR et al., 2016). The newly described species are highlighted in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982839" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982839/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The male and female genitalia confirm this classification and this species is described below as new under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C672A87FF88FF901F2FF974FB06F3DF" authority="Laguerre" authorityName="Laguerrre" authorityYear="2021" box="[863,1208,1739,1765]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drechseli" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF901F2FF974FBF2F3DF" box="[863,1100,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">Robinsonia drechseli</emphasis>
Laguerre
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9138D16FF88FF9018CFF974FAA6F3DF" bold="true" box="[1215,1304,1739,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A220306DFF88FF9018CFF974FAA6F3DF" box="[1215,1304,1739,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
